               <h2><b>Healthy cooking Tips</b></h2>
               <div>
                  <ul>
                     <li>
                        <p>Wash vegetables before peeling or cutting to remove dirt and germs.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Always soak cauliflower in warm salted water for some time to get rid of the tiny insects 
                           that may be present deep inside the florets and are not visible to the eye.
                        </p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Do not use baking soda for cooking pulses and vegetables as it destroys Vitamins A and B.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Select oils that provide omega-3 fatty acids and antioxidants, such as Olive oil or Soyabean oil.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Use finally chopped spinach in dals and vegetables curries instead of chopped coriander. It is more nutritious and rich in iron content</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
               <h2><b>Vegetarian Cooking Tips</b></h2>
               <div>
                  <ul>
                     <li>
                        <p>If you boil vegetables in water, do not throw the water, keep it to make gravies.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>After peeling the onions cut in half and soak in water for about 10 minutes before cutting to avoid crying.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Soak potatoes after cutting to avoid discoloration.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Before grinding green chillies, soak them so that they soften and make a fine paste.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>To prevent biryani or rice from sticking to the bottom of the pan and getting burnt, spread a layer of bay leaves at the bottom of the utensil before layering the rice and meat or vegetables in it.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
               <h2><b>Non-Vegetarian Cooking Tips</b></h2>
               <div>
                  <ul>
                     <li>
                        <p>Bringing eggs to room temperature prior to beating them improves aeration.Your omlellets will turn out to be much better.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>When you cook chicken or meat, you should first cook over high heat to seal juices and then lower the heat and cook till tender.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>To avoid kebabs from becoming hard and chewy, marinate them for a longer time and avoid over cooking them.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Sprinkle a little amount of salt in the frying pan before adding bacon to fry. That way it will not splatter all over.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
               <h2><b>Food Storage Tips</b></h2>
               <div>
                  <ul>
                     <li>
                        <p>Add a few grains of rice to your salt container to prevent salt from sticking together during periods of high humidity.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Unripe avocados develop brown spots and fail to ripen further.So best to store them in a cool and dark place.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>To prevent insects from getting inside the rice and dal containers, put a few neem leaves inside the containers.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Do not store the potatoes and onions together as it causes eyes in the potatoes.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Never put citrus fruits in the fridge as the low temperatures degrade the aroma and flavor of these fruits.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
